<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/freeform"
  i18n:domain="launchpad">
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <div class="informational message" tal:condition="view/canRedirect">
    <tal:redirect_inhibited condition="view/isRedirectInhibited">
      <p>As a member of the Launchpad Beta Testers team, you would
      normally be redirected to the beta site when viewing Launchpad
      pages.  However, you currently have this disabled.</p>
      <p><button onclick="setBetaRedirect(true)">Enable beta site
      redirection</button></p>
    </tal:redirect_inhibited>
    <tal:redirect_enabled condition="not:view/isRedirectInhibited">
      <p>As a member of the Launchpad Beta Testers team, you will be
      redirected to the beta site when viewing Launchpad pages other
      than the front page.</p>
      <p><button onclick="setBetaRedirect(false)">Disable redirection
      for 2 hours</button></p>
    </tal:redirect_enabled>
  </div>

      <div id="applications" tal:content="structure context/@@+applicationbuttons/main" />
      <form
        class="central front_page"
        style="text-align: center;"
        action="/projects/"
        method="get"
        accept-charset="UTF-8"
      >
        <tal:comment replace="nothing">
          Do not replace the line below: "Is your project registered yet?"
          without contacting the IS team. It's used by Nagios to verify
          the app servers are running.
        </tal:comment>
        <label for="text">Is your project registered yet?</label>
        <input id="text" type="text" name="text" size="20" />
        <input type="submit" value="Search" />
      </form>

        <div class="three column left">
          <h2>What is Launchpad?</h2>
          <p id="application-summary">
            Launchpad is a free software hosting and development
            website. We make it easy to <strong>collaborate
            across multiple projects</strong>.
            <br />
            <center>
              <a href="/+about">
                <img
                  alt="Take a tour"
                  src="/+icing/but-lrg-takeatour.gif"
                />
              </a>
            </center>
          </p>
          <tal:not-beta-team-member condition="not: view/isBetaUser">
           <h2>Join the Launchpad beta team</h2>
           <p id="beta-test">
            Get first access to new features and take part in the Launchpad development process.
            Join the <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/BetaTesting">beta team</a> today!
           </p>
          </tal:not-beta-team-member>
        </div>
        <div class="three column middle">
          <h2>What&#8217;s new here?</h2>
          <ul>
            <li class="news">
              <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/PPAQuickStart#copy">
                <strong>Copy PPA packages</strong><br />
                Now you can copy source and binary packages between distro
                releases within a PPA or to any other PPA for which you
                have upload permission.
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="news">
              <a href="http://news.launchpad.net/?p=66">
                <strong>Meet the bug supervisor</strong><br />
                Bug contacts are now called bug supervisors. Read our blog
                post to find out why.
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="news">
              <a href="https://code.launchpad.net/+recently-imported-branches">
                <strong>View recent code imports</strong><br />
                See the status of all Subversion and CVS imports into
                Launchpad, including their most recent commit messages.
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="news">
              <a href="https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+ppas">
                <strong>Improved PPA distro overview page</strong><br />
                Our new distro PPA overview page highlights the most active
                archives and the latest PPA uploads, along with supported
                architectures and distribution releases.
               </a>
            </li>
            <li class="news">
              <a href="http://news.launchpad.net/?p=57">
                <strong>Mailing lists for teams!</strong><br />
                Each team in Launchpad can now have its own mailing list,
                with full public archives.
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="discreet" style="text-align: right">
            Updated 2008-04-30.
            <a href="http://news.launchpad.net">More...</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="three column right" id="featured-projects">
          <h2>Featured projects</h2>
          <table>
            <tr tal:repeat="project view/featured_projects">
              <td tal:content="structure project/fmt:link" />
            </tr>
          </table>
          <ul tal:condition="not: view/featured_projects">
            <li class="product"><a href="/exaile">Exaile Media Player</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/deluge">Deluge Torrent Client</a></li>
            <li class="distro"><a href="/ubuntu">Ubuntu</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/bzr">Bazaar Version Control</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/democracy">Miro TV Player</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/awn">Avant Window Navigator</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/schooltool">SchoolTool</a></li>
            <li class="product"><a href="/tangocms">TangoCMS</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <a tal:condition="context/required:launchpad.Admin"
               href="+featuredprojects">&raquo; Manage featured project list</a>
          </p>
        </div>
    </div><!--main-->
    <div metal:fill-slot="help">
      <p>
      This panel provides help on individual Launchpad pages.
      Open it on any page that you don&rsquo;t understand.
      </p>
      <p>
      You can browse our dedicated help site, <a
      href="https://help.launchpad.net/">help.launchpad.net</a>, for a
      complete set of documents about Launchpad
      </p>
      <p>
      You can also find help on the <a
      href="https://lists.ubuntu.com/mailman/listinfo/launchpad-users">Launchpad
      users mailing list</a> or online via IRC, on <a
      href="http://freenode.net/">Freenode</a>, channel #launchpad.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
<!-- 1-0 done could use a team icon though -->
